Reviews.Title: So Far So Good!
Reviews.Author: Tony Coppola
Reviews.Content: The Fast Processor is great. Well worth the money. I run my Business on it which involves MS Office Spreadsheets, Word etc and this performs very smooth and fast enough for me. Extremely easy to set up .(CHOOSE MANUAL SETUP DO NOT LET HP CHOOSE FOR YOU, YOU WILL GET LOADED WITH JUNK APPS) I find the machine to be more than fast enough to Stream Video, work on Spreadsheets (MS Office is not included, that's why I gave it a 4 instead of a 5) Using it as a Tablet is very good, the touch screen is very accurate, make sure you calibrate it in settings. I do miss the 3rd USB port as it has 1- 2.0 Port and 1-3.0 a 3rd as most have would have been nice. Windows 8 does take time to get use to. I personally have no problems with Windows 8 as I have been using it for months. Go to Classicshell.net and download to get the old Start Button Back and it will all feel the same to XP users. I don't use the Metro part of Windows much at all, and with The Classic Shell Start Button it feels just like Old Windows. I recommend this Highly and would purchase again. Its only been a day but so far so good, Ill update if there are any problems.

Reviews.Title: Laptop
Reviews.Author: Roy Dixon
Reviews.Content: I am really enjoying the 2-n-1 touchscreen laptop.  Small, easy to carry and the magnetic connections work great to separate the laptop from screen to utilize it as a tablet.  The battery life is working good for approximate 5.5 hours.  I moved from a 17" heavy laptop, which I gave to my granddaughter, as it was too cumbersome to lug around.  Very happy.

Reviews.Title: great computer
Reviews.Author: anthony
Reviews.Content: It is an awesome computer and a great value. I gave it a four because there are no usb ports on tablet section and it's light weight comes with a sacrifice of power. For a student this is a great buy in that It combines so many features in a small package.

Reviews.Title: Not as great as I'd hoped, but still pretty great
Reviews.Author: Hannah
Reviews.Content: I decided to buy this laptop because I've wanted a hybrid for school for a while now. My Acer Aspire netbook still works fine, so I decided I'll have that one for games but it's so bulky it wasn't practical to use for school.Pros:Very clear pictureEasy to use keyboardResponsive touch screenWindows 8 isn't as annoying as I thought it would beCons:A bit heavier than I expectedGreat size for a netbook, kind of big for a tabletThe track pad is kind of unresponsiveNot a ton of apps for windows 8 yetThe edge digs into your legs when you have it on your lapOverall, I'm happy with the purchase, but I'm having kind of a hard time adjusting to this laptop instead. Part of that is the new OS, part of it is just getting used to something new. As I type this I also realize the keys feel different than my old laptop, and that's a bit unnerving. But, still a good decision to buy.Oh, and I'm not sure if the 5.5 hour battery life is a pro or a con. My Acer doesn't last 45 minutes off the cord anymore, so it's a huge plus for me to have the battery life, but I know some people want longer battery life.This also comes pre installed with a lot of apps you've gotta dig through and get rid of if you don't want them, but after you have it all set up it's a nice machine.Tips: I've had this laptop for a few months now, here's how you can make it work smoother for you.1) Uninstall the browser safeguard, it doesn't actually help you, and it ruins web browsing.2) I can't remember exactly how, but turn off the setting that brings up the menus on the side when your mouse scrolls over to it. You'll be much happier (I think it's in the synaptics pad file, play around a bit)

Reviews.Title: 11 inch HP convertible is the best tablet for the money
Reviews.Author: MarkV
Reviews.Content: I have had this laptop for about 4 weeks.  Its a great size for a tablet, slightly larger than the Ipad and about the same weight. I first purchased the 13 inch 2 in 1, but returned it (Best Buy) when I found the tablet was a little too big and heavy.  I use it mostly as a tablet, but I will use it as a laptop when traveling. It is fast enough for typical use and the screen has good resolution and operates well.  Battery life is less than an Ipad, so I dock it every couple days. The only negatives are that Windows 8.1 is a little hard to get used to and the camera has no flash, so indoor pictures are somewhat grainy.

Reviews.Title: Great 2 in 1
Reviews.Author: R. J. Wilson "R. Wilson"
Reviews.Content: I really like this laptop.  If gives me the flexibility that I was looking for from this device.  The only complaint that I have is that the battery does not hold a charge for as long as advertised.  It is still not bad, and I can live with that as I was not planning on using it like a tablet all the time.  The other complaint that i have is that I have not been able to find a cover or shell for it, but that is not a Laptop issue.

Reviews.Title: Great little machine for the price....
Reviews.Author: scoobydoo
Reviews.Content: If you are looking at getting a combo tablet / laptop this machine seems to work quite nicely.  First time using Window s 8.  You have to get used to it.

Reviews.Title: Works as Expected
Reviews.Author: SHELLEY SUSMAN
Reviews.Content: I really like the size and feel of the machine. The SSD is a real plus. As in most machines, you have to uninstall the bloat, but it runs well. I will be using it for hospital work and have to carry it around, so its size was important. Good machine for the money. I would recommend it,

Reviews.Title: not very good at multitasking
Reviews.Author: Trevor Smith
Reviews.Content: after owning this for a week I am still very happy and excited about it.  It's defenitely worth the amazon price, not so much the suggested retail... The one problem I am having is multitasking, I had to train dragon six times because the profile set up kept being interupted by something else, once interupted it would simply stay on "not responding" for hours,  I litterally had to close everything else and turn off wifi in order for the task to complete.  Secondly while transffering large portions of data, 30 gigs or so, the data transfer would get interupted if I tried surfing the net at the same time, but that might be because I bought a cheap sd card.  Also, keep in mind that you'll only have about 27 gigs of free space to start with, so one or two 64gb sd cards are a must to keep the main hard drive available for software installations.

Reviews.Title: Less than I hoped for
Reviews.Author: Alison
Reviews.Content: I'm contemplating returning this item.  The keys don't react well to typing; so I have to retype or tap again after I've written something.  Also; I am not sure if it's a Windows 8.1 issue or not; but when I'm moving my mouse around it will randomly switch screens.  I hate Windows 8.1... it's hard to navigate. It's more like a cell phone with "apps" for the different programs that you need.Cons:Typing on this keyboard is awful.Randomly switching screens without being prompted.Because the screen detaches, it doesn't go back far enough, so I have to type or operate it at an awkward angle. Ironically, it isn't a good "lap-top."Be careful which hardshell case you buy with this; the HP 11.6 Envy iPearl case doesn't fit this computer. It was under the "often bought with this item" in amazon; so I figured it would fit... but it doesn't.  It's just shy of the same shape.The mouse is VERY sensitive.  It highlights and deletes words without prompting; just if your hands happen to touch it at the wrong angle.  People with larger palms would probably get annoyed very quickly.Pros:Battery life is surprisingly long.The on-screen typing for the detachable screen is surprisingly nice.  It's very reactive.It's all in all a 'nice' laptop; and will get the job done for what I bought it for.The price is pretty good for what you get.I think the laptop will grow on me; it's just taking more time to get used to. I'm weighing the pros/cons.  I really liked my Toshiba satellite.  That computer was AWESOME for the money...
